Chief Petty Officer Lance Vickery recalls

At least 19 sailors drowned, and scores were injured.
Vickery, 33, was among four American sailors interviewed at Haifa's Rambam Hospital.
He is from Jacksonville, Fla., is not far from Mayport, the Saragota's home port.
"I started breathing in water and almost died," Vickery said.
One rescue boat, already overloaded, passed by and threw life preservers.
Two other men interviewed at Rambam Hospital identified themselves as Technician John Richards, 31, of Twin Lake, Mich., and Airman Lamont Jones, 20, of Claremont, Va.
